description: Israeli Defense Minister Yoav Gallant urged US Secretary of State Antony Blinken to support the country in its conflict with Hezbollah in neighboring Lebanon, saying the world is watching for signs of strain in the relationship between the two allies.
title: Israel’s Gallant Calls on US to Support Conflict With Hezbollah

description: Wikileaks co-founder Julian Assange is on a plane to Saipan where he will plead guilty to leaking US national security data as part of a deal that will allow him to return to his home country of Australia.
title: Wikileaks’ Assange Headed to Saipan to Plead Guilty in US Case

description: On paper, New York’s 1st Congressional district reads like a winner for Democrats. For one, it’s home to more of them than registered Republicans. And its voters favor abortion access for women, care deeply about the environment and boast high levels of union membership.
title: From the Hamptons to the Bronx, New York Democrats Fight Primaries

description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy replaced one of his top generals following harsh criticism in social media over setbacks on the frontline and claims of an unnecessary high death toll among the soldiers under his command.
title: Zelenskiy Replaces Head of Ukraine’sTroops in East Amid Russia’s Advances

description: Marine Le Pen said French President Emmanuel Macron’s accusations that the agendas of the far right National Rally and leftist alliance could lead to “civil war” indicate that he knows he’s going to lose the upcoming legislative vote that begins on Sunday.
title: Le Pen Brands Macron’s ‘Civil War’ Comment as Scaremongering
